# Axis 24 — multi-shot control copies control, not the heap

The reusable continuation runs twice. Both resumes share the ordinary mutable
cell captured by the suffix, so the branches observe `1` and then `2`; this is
deliberately not an implicit heap snapshot.

```scalascript
multi effect Choose:
  def choose(): Boolean

var cell = 0

val results = handle {
  val ignored = Choose.choose()
  cell = cell + 1
  List(cell)
} {
  case Choose.choose(resume) => resume(true) ++ resume(false)
}

println(results)
println(cell)
```
